<h2>The Internship</h2>
<div id="accordion3" class="accordion">
	<h3 class="accordion-toggle accordion-heading">What will I be doing during my internship?</h3>
	<div class="accordion-inner faq-border">
		<p>During your four-week internship you will have the opportunity to apply your newly-learned skills in the real world.</p>
		<p>This not only provides an exciting opportunity to cement the concepts you will have been taught in class, but also gain work experience in an area that interests you. We give you exposure to dozens of high-profile companies, so you’re sure to find work that aligns with your abilities and interests.</p>
    <h3>Here's what the internships are like:</h3>
		<div class='videowrapper'>
			<iframe width="100%" height="400" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/AwcVEY7dLj4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
		</div>
	</div>

	<h3 class="accordion-toggle accordion-heading">How do I get placed into an internship?</h3>
	<div class="accordion-inner faq-border">
		<p>During the the first four weeks of the program iXperience will host a Company Intern Information Night, during which we will present more information about each company and the kind of work you would do there. Each student then submits short applications for up to three companies at which they would like to intern. With the guidance of your professors and teaching assistants, our internship team places each student according to his or her skill set, interests and preferences. You will always be placed alongside at least one other iXperience student.</p>-
	</div>

